<TEXT>
vincent van goghs melancholy portrait of the 
doctor who treated him in the weeks before his suicide sold at 
auction for 825 million making it by far the most expensive 
painting in the world 
the sale tuesday of portrait of dr gachet came after a 
10minute bidding war at christies auction house between two 
buyers who jacked up the price in increments of 1 million 
the 26by225inch oil was worth 141000 per square inch to 
kobayashi gallery of tokyo which has emerged in recent years as a 
major buyer of impressionist art 
the total surpassed the 539 million paid for van goghs 
irises in 1987 at sothebys said susan britman a christies 
spokeswoman 
explaining the astronomical price christies president 
christopher burge cited the paintings good condition its 
highprofile exhibitions in new york and the opinion among many 
