owned by the trust of germanborn banker siegfried kramarsky 
who died in 1961 portrait of dr gachet had hung since 1984 at 
the metropolitan museum of art christies had expected it to fetch 
between 40 million and 50 million 
the painting was completed in auverssuroise france six weeks 
before the artists suicide in 1890 dr paulferdinand gachet a 
practitioner of homeopathic medicine and a friend and physician to 
other impressionist painters had tended to van gogh in the final 
weeks of his life 
